--- [RESPONSE] (8.2s) ---
### File Structure
```
RestaurantReservation/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── menu.html
│   ├── dish_details.html
│   ├── make_reservation.html
│   ├── my_reservations.html
│   ├── waitlist.html
│   ├── my_reviews.html
│   ├── write_review.html
│   └── profile.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   └── images/
│       └── (dish images and other assets)
│
└── data/
    ├── users.txt
    ├── menu.txt
    ├── reservations.txt
    ├── waitlist.txt
    └── reviews.txt
```

### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main backend Python file implementing the web application using a web framework (e.g., Flask). 
  It handles routing for all nine pages, processes user inputs, reads from and writes to the local text files in the 'data' directory, and manages the application logic.

- templates/
  Directory containing HTML template files for each page of the web application. Each file corresponds to one of the nine pages defined in the requirements:
    - dashboard.html: Dashboard page layout and elements.
    - menu.html: Menu page with dish listings and filtering.
    - dish_details.html: Detailed view of a selected dish.
    - make_reservation.html: Form for making a reservation.
    - my_reservations.html: Displays user's reservations with cancellation options.
    - waitlist.html: Waitlist management page.
    - my_reviews.html: Lists user's reviews.
    - write_review.html: Form to write a new review.
    - profile.html: User profile view and edit page.

- static/
  Contains static assets such as CSS stylesheets and images.
    - css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
    - images/: Folder for dish images and other graphical assets used in the UI.

- data/
  Stores all application data in text files as specified:
    - users.txt: User information.
    - menu.txt: Restaurant menu items.
    - reservations.txt: Reservation records.
    - waitlist.txt: Waitlist entries.
    - reviews.txt: User reviews.

This structure keeps backend logic centralized in one Python file for simplicity, while separating frontend templates and static assets for maintainability and clarity. The data directory ensures organized local storage of all persistent data.
```
